## Voice Rules (Non-Negotiable)

- **No emdashes.** Use commas, periods, colons, parentheses, or ellipses.
- **No semicolons.** Use commas.
- **No AI-isms.** Banned phrases: "cautiously optimistic", "it is important to note", "going forward", "in our view", "at the end of the day", "complex constellation of factors", "nuanced picture", "multifaceted".
- **"We" not "the data shows".** Speak as Lighthouse Macro.
- **Short sentences control rhythm.** Use them to land punches.
- **Dry observations, not forced flair.** "The labor data softened. Again." beats any metaphor.
- **Strong views, weakly held.** State the thesis clearly. State what would break it. Don't hedge.

---

## Chart Rules

- 5 charts per Beam. Not 4, not 6.
- All charts use the 23/89/BB palette (Ocean, Dusk, Sky, Venus, Sea, Doldrums, Starboard, Port, Fog).
- White theme primary. 4pt Ocean border. All four spines visible. No gridlines.
- Last-value pills on primary axis. X-axis padding for pill room (30 days left, 180 days right minimum).
- Source footer: `Lighthouse Macro | {source agency} | Data thru {date} | Pulled {date}`
- Chart captions below the chart, centered, Inter 9-10pt, "Figure N: Description"

